PMC Housekeeping System

Admin User Guide  ·  July 2025  ·  Philsaga Mining Corporation

This guide covers all features available to Admin users of the PMC Housekeeping Checklist Monitoring System — from signing in and managing your account, to reviewing weekly checklists, generating reports, and configuring system maintenance settings.
CH 01

Getting Started

Q
What is the PMC Housekeeping System?

The PMC Housekeeping Checklist Monitoring System is a customized, user-friendly portal that helps manage and track weekly housekeeping inspections across all departments and working areas. It contains all the essential tools for creating, submitting, reviewing, and reporting on checklists.

Admin Note: Only the Admin Role can view all data across all departments and locations in the portal.
Q
How do I sign in to the Housekeeping Portal?
  1. Go to the web address of the Housekeeping Portal.
  2. Enter your Email address.
  3. Enter your Password.
  4. Click the Continue button to log in.

Sign-In page — Housekeeping Checklist Monitoring System

Q
How do I reset my password if I've forgotten it?
  1. On the Sign-In page, click Forgot Password?
  2. The Forgot Password page appears. Enter your email address and click Continue.
  3. Check your inbox for a Reset Your Password email from PMC House Keeping. Click the Reset Password button in the email. Note: the link expires in 60 minutes.
  4. On the Reset Password page, enter and confirm your new password (minimum 8 characters).
  5. Click Reset Password to complete the process.

Forgot Password page

Password reset email from PMC House Keeping

Reset Password form — minimum 8 characters required

Q
How do I change my password from within the portal?
  1. Click the Account icon at the top-right of the screen.
  2. Select Profile.
  3. In the Change Password section, enter and confirm your new password.
  4. Click Update Password to save.
Important: You will be logged out immediately after changing your password and must log back in using your new credentials.
Q
How do I sign out of the portal?
  1. Click the Account icon at the top-right of the screen.
  2. Click Log Out.
CH 02

Dashboard

Q
What does the Dashboard show and how is it organized?

The Dashboard gives a quick overview of the current status of all weekly checklists and activities. It is organized into three main sections:

  • Weekly Data — Displays color-coded week tiles for up to 12 past weeks, along with key stats: Total Locations, Submitted Locations, and Pending Locations for the selected week.
  • Weekly Submission Performance — A bar chart showing on-time, late, and missed submissions per week, plus a table of Locations with Most Late/Missing Reports.
  • Recent Submitted Weekly Checklists — A table of the most recent submissions with department, location, date, and status.

Dashboard — Weekly Data section showing 30th week of 2025

Dashboard — Weekly Submission Performance chart and Recent Submitted Checklists

Tip: Hover over any week tile to see additional details and quick actions for that week.
CH 03

Weekly Checklists

Q
What is the Weekly Checklists module and how do I navigate it?

The Weekly Checklists module displays all submitted weekly inspection checklists with details such as department, working area, inspection date/time, and submission status. As Admin, you can see checklists from all departments.

Go to Menu → Weekly Checklists. Use the filters (Week #, Year, Department, Location, Status) to search for specific checklists. Each row in the list has action buttons: Print, View, and Edit.

Submitted Weekly Checklists — Admin view with all departments and status filters

Q
How do I print a weekly checklist?
  1. Go to Menu → Weekly Checklists.
  2. Locate the checklist using the Filter. Use Week #, Year, Department, and Location to narrow your search.
  3. Click the Print icon (printer symbol) in the Actions column.
  4. A new browser tab opens with the checklist in PDF view.
  5. Click Print to send to a printer, or click the Download icon to save as a PDF file.

Weekly Checklists list — Print icon in the Actions column

Checklist PDF view — click Print or use the download icon

Q
How do I view the details of a submitted checklist?
  1. Go to Menu → Weekly Checklists and locate the checklist.
  2. Click the View icon (eye symbol) in the Actions column.
  3. The Checklist Details page opens, showing the date and time of inspection, inspector name, location/working area, overall status, remarks, and all inspection checklist items with their Yes/No/N/A responses.
  4. You can also print directly from this view using the Print icon at the top right.

Checklist Details — shows inspection info, status badge, and all checklist items

Q
How do I edit a submitted weekly checklist?
  1. Go to Menu → Weekly Checklists and locate the checklist to edit.
  2. Click the Edit icon (pencil symbol) in the Actions column.
  3. The Edit Inspection Checklist Transaction page opens. You can update the Date of Inspection, Time, and Location.
  4. Review each checklist item and select Yes, No, N/A, or Incorrectly Marked. When selecting No, a remarks field appears — enter a remark before continuing.
  5. You may also upload and attach photos as proof for each checklist section.
  6. Enter a final remark at the bottom.
  7. Click Update to save all changes.

Edit Inspection Checklist — select Yes/No/N/A per item; No triggers a remarks field

CH 04

Reports

Q
What reports are available and how do I access them?

The Reports module provides monitoring reports on checklist submissions across all areas. Go to Menu → Reports to access the following:

  • Weekly Monitoring — Full matrix of all locations by week, showing submission status (✓ on-time, ✗ missed).
  • Monthly & Quarterly Monitoring — Sub-reports by Division or Department, available in Monthly or Quarterly views.

All reports support Export Excel Report for downloading data, and most support year/quarter/month filters.

Q
How do I view and export the Weekly Monitoring Report?
  1. Go to Reports → Weekly Monitoring.
  2. The Weekly Housekeeping Inspection Checklist Monitoring screen shows the full grid of all surface and underground locations vs. weekly submission status.
  3. Scroll down to see the summary section and Total Percentage of On-Time Submission.
  4. Click Export Excel Report to download as an .xlsx file. Save it to your device.

Weekly Housekeeping Inspection Checklist Monitoring — shows all locations vs. weekly status

Save As dialog — export saved as Weekly_Housekeeping_FullReport_[date].xlsx

Q
How do I view the Monthly & Quarterly Monitoring reports?

Go to Reports → Monthly & Quarterly Monitoring. Use the tabs at the top to choose the report type:

  • Quarterly Division — Shows WHI monitoring per division (timely, late, no submission counts) for a selected year and quarter.
  • Monthly Division — Summary of monthly monitoring per division for a selected month and year.
  • Quarterly Department — WHI monitoring per department/section for a selected quarter.
  • Monthly Department — Summary per department for a selected month.

Use the Year and Quarter/Month dropdowns to filter, then click Apply Filters. Click Export Excel Report to download.

Quarterly Division report — filter by Year and Quarter, export to Excel

CH 05

Maintenance

Q
What is the Maintenance module and what can be configured?

The Maintenance module lets Admin users configure system settings that affect all other modules. You can create, edit, view, and delete records in five areas:

  • Checklist Categories — Define inspection categories (e.g., Walkways, Lighting, Safety) and their checklist items.
  • Locations / Areas — Manage working areas and assign them to departments.
  • Users — Create and manage user accounts, roles, and location assignments.
  • Divisions — Group departments into divisions (Surface or Underground).
  • Cutoffs — View weekly cutoff periods (start and end dates per week number).
Warning: Deletion in all Maintenance areas is permanent. There is no restore function once an item is deleted.
Q
How do I manage Checklist Categories?

Go to Maintenance → Checklist Categories. The list shows all categories with their description, sequence number, and action buttons.

Checklist Categories list — shows 11 categories including Walkways, Lighting, Safety, Health

To create: Click + Create. Fill in the Category Description, Sequence Number, Forms (Surface/Underground), and add Checklist items with their individual sequence numbers and form types. Click Save.

To edit: Click the Edit icon, update all fields, and click Update.

Edit Checklist Category — update description, sequence, form types, and individual checklist items

To view: Click the View icon to see the full category details.

To delete: Click the Delete icon (red), confirm with OK in the pop-up. Deletion is permanent.

Q
How do I manage Location / Working Areas?

Go to Maintenance → Location / Areas. The list displays all working areas with their Type (Surface/Underground) and assigned Department.

Location / Working Areas — searchable and filterable by Type and Department

To create: Click + Create. Fill in the Location Area Name, Form type (Surface or Underground), and assign it to a Department. Click Create.

To edit: Use Search or Filter to find the area, click the Edit icon, update the fields, and click Update.

To view: Click the View icon.

To delete: Click the Delete icon and confirm with OK. Permanent — no restore.

Q
How do I manage Users?

Go to Maintenance → Users. The Users list shows all system accounts with their name, email, position, role, and department.

Users list — shows ID, Name, Email, Position, Role, Department, and action buttons

To create: Click + Create. Fill in: First Name, Last Name, Email Address, Position, Department, Role, and Location Areas. Click Create.

To edit: Use Search or Filter (by Role or Department) to find the user, click the Edit icon, update fields, and click Update.

Edit User form — update name, email, position, department, role, and location areas

To view: Click the View icon to see the user's full profile.

To delete: Click the Delete icon and confirm with OK. Permanent — no restore.

Q
How do I manage Divisions?

Go to Maintenance → Divisions. Divisions group departments and define whether they belong to the Surface or Underground form type.

Divisions list — shows Division Name, Type, and all assigned Department tags

To create: Click + Create. Enter the Division Name, Description, and assign Departments from the available selections. Click Save.

To edit: Find the division using Search or Filter, click the Edit icon, update the fields, and click Update.

To delete: Click the Delete icon and confirm with OK. Permanent — no restore.

Q
How do I view Cutoffs?

Go to Maintenance → Cutoffs. The Cutoffs screen lists all configured weekly submission periods, showing the Week Number, Date Start, and Date End for each cutoff.

Cutoffs — weekly submission periods with start and end dates (paginated)

Use the Pagination controls to navigate through all cutoff records. Cutoffs define the valid date range for each weekly checklist submission.
